frameDefinitions: A Complex with a particular Function is formed out of Component_entities.
This frame describes a complex event which lasts some amount of time, consisting of a beginning stage, a stage where the process is ongoing, and a finish or end.
An Agent has a choice of whether or not to participate in some Desirable_event because of an Opportunity, a situation not completely under the Agent's control and usually of a limited duration.
An Agent suddenly and often violently separates the Whole_patient into two or more smaller Pieces, resulting in the Whole_patient no longer existing as such.
An Entity meets the pre-conditions for participating in an Event.
A stretch of linguistic discourse or a Text that a Communicator produces has a Topic that it is about.
frameExamples: The body's immune <t>system</t> can be mobilized against cancer.
I'm in the <t>process</t> of writing it down.
It would be pleasant in the <t>opportune</t> absence of the clergyman to have a dance . DNI
He <t>ripped</t> <t>up</t> the letter faster than you can say 'Jack Robbins'. INI
Conductor software gives us the hands-on <t>capability</t> to provide updates immediately
listRoleDefinitions: The entities that function together as a unit.
The unit formed by the <fen>Component_entities</fen>.
The activity that the <fen>Complex</fen> entity performs by virtue of its <fen>Component_entities</fen> interacting.
The kind of entity that the <fen>Complex</fen> operates on as part of its <fen>Function</fen>.
Name of the Process which occurs.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The situation during which the <fen>Desirable_situation</fen> is possible. For nominal LUs, this is generally in the second layer and contains the target.
The sentient agent that may or may not participate in the <fen>Desirable_situation</fen>.
A situation or event that the <fen>Agent</fen> can participating in during the period of the <fen>Opportunity</fen>.
The conscious entity, generally a person, that performs the intentional action that results in the <fen>Whole_patient</fen> being broken into <fen>Pieces</fen>.
The entity which is destroyed by the <fen>Agent</fen> and that ends up broken into <fen>Pieces</fen>.
The fragments of the <fen>Whole_patient</fen> that result from the <fen>Agent</fen>'s action.
An event which leads to the fragmentation of the <fen>Whole_patient</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> breaks up the <fen>Whole_patient</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> breaks the <fen>Whole_patient</fen> into pieces.
The <fen>Entity</fen> whose meeting or falling short of pre-conditions is assessed.
The <fen>Event</fen> that the <fen>Entity</fen> may participate in.
The time at which the <fen>Entity</fen> is capable of the <fen>Event</fen>.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is what a <fen>Text</fen> is about.
A set of propositions that is coherent in being about a <fen>Topic</fen>
The <fen>Communicator</fen> is the person who has produced a <fen>Text</fen> on a <fen>Topic</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Communicator</fen> produces <fen>Text</fen> on a <fen>Topic</fen>.
